<br>
1. Prisons - The legalization of marijuana will free up jail cells for those convicted of marijuana based crimes. The empty cells will alleviate the tax burden on american for the $40,000  a year it takes to confine these people.<br>
<br>
2. Courts - By removing the minor drug possesion offenses from the courts will greatly speed up the time in which a major criminal case can be run through the system. No more year long pauses between indictment and trial.<br>
<br>
3. Quality Control - Government grown and sold marijuana could be regulated for quality so there are no more instances of a person wanting to get a little high and end up posioned with laced marijuana.<br>
<br>
4. Taxation - Much like cigarettes, the taxes from the legalized sale of marijuana could be used for a number of social programs to help better the american populace as a whole.<br>
<br>
5 Crime - If marijuana was legalized and sold through government distribution centers, the prices normally paid on the street would go down, negating the need for petty crimes to garner the cash needed to get it.<br>
<br>
6. Police - Since the police would no longer have to go after marijuana smokers, they would have more time to focus their attention on more important issues such as child molesters, murderers, and those dealing in dangerous drugs.<br>
<br>
Tell me your thoughts. <p><a href=mailto:Dandaelus@allakhazam.com>Dandaelus Wyldheart</a>
